# Implementation Plan - Fix Empty AI Analysis Results

The user wants to perform conformity analysis by comparing an uploaded document (e.g., CERFA) directly against a reference PLU document uploaded in the "Espace Conformité", instead of requiring a pre-existing property analysis.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Improvements

#### [MODIFY] [pluAnalysis.ts](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/services/pluAnalysis.ts)
- Upgrade the AI model from `gpt-4o-mini` to `gpt-4o` to ensure better extraction accuracy for complex PLU documents (like Étretat).

#### [MODIFY] [documentReviews.ts](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/lib/db/src/schema/documentReviews.ts)
- Add `commune: text("commune")` to `documentReviewsTable`.

#### [MODIFY] [documents.ts](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/documents.ts)
- Add logging to track why comparison might be skipped or fail.
- Ensure that if `analysisId` is provided, the comparison is triggered.
- Update [compare](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/documents.ts#130-197) endpoint to accept `referenceDocumentId`.
- If `referenceDocumentId` is provided, fetch its extracted text and use it as the PLU context for comparison.
- Maintain support for `analysisId` as an alternative context source.
- Update `upload` and [compare](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/documents.ts#130-197) endpoints to accept and store `commune`.
- Update comparison logic to fetch `townHallDocuments` and `townHallPrompts` based on the document's `commune` if no `analysisId` is provided.

### Prompt Improvements

#### [MODIFY] [document_extract prompt](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/services/promptLoader.ts)
- Refine extraction logic to be more specific to French CERFA forms (Permis de construire, DP, etc.).

### Frontend - Espace Conformité

#### [MODIFY] [mairie.tsx](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/heureka/src/pages/mairie.tsx)
- Add a selection dropdown in the "Déposer un document" (Upload) form to allow users to link the document to an existing property analysis.
- Use the [useAdminListAnalyses](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/lib/api-client-react/src/generated/api.ts#1738-1760) or similar hook to fetch available analyses.
- Update [handleUpload](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/heureka/src/pages/mairie.tsx#113-148) to include the selected `analysisId` in the `FormData`.
- Improve the UI for documents that have no linked analysis, allowing users to link them after the fact using the existing `compareMutation`.
- Add "PLU (Référence)" (`plu_reference`) to the document types.
- Update the comparison UI to allow selecting either an "Analyse de parcelle" OR a "Document de référence" from the list of uploaded documents.
- Filter the "Document de référence" list to only show documents of type `plu_reference`.
- Update `compareMutation` and [handleUpload](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/heureka/src/pages/mairie.tsx#113-148) to support `referenceDocumentId`.

